  title: `Artificial Intelligence, Care Ethics, and Technology`,
  subtitle: `When the machine you ask for help is also the one that sees you most clearly.`,
  summary: `Care ethics as a lens for AI systems that mediate emotional, medical, and educational life. What caregivers owe, what recipients need, and what code can carry.`,
  learningGoals: [`Articulate care ethics as a distinct ethical tradition with its own core commitments.`, `Evaluate AI caregiving systems on attentiveness, responsibility, competence, and responsiveness.`, `Design AI services whose relationship to the user is honest, bounded, and nourishing.`],
